---
const resumePath = "/Sara_Rajabzadeh_Resume.pdf";

const icmTags = [
	"Medical Imaging",
	"nnU-Net v2",
	"Active Learning",
	"Napari",
	"SLURM",
	"Instance Segmentation",
];

const epflTags = [
	"Diffusion Models",
	"3D Human Pose",
	"PyTorch",
	"Generative Modeling",
	"ICRA 2023",
];

const iqaTags = [
	"Image Quality Assessment",
	"Face Quality",
	"PyTorch",
	"FastAPI",
	"Docker",
	"CUDA",
];

const uclTags = [
	"Medical AI",
	"X-ray Imaging",
	"EfficientNet",
	"Grad-CAM",
	"Clinical Research",
];
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="UTF-8" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />

		<title>Projects — Sara Rajabzadeh</title>

		<meta
			name="description"
			content="Selected computer vision, medical imaging, generative modeling, and machine-learning engineering projects by Sara Rajabzadeh."
		/>

		<meta name="theme-color" content="#07090d" />

		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
	</head>

	<body>
		<div class="page-background" aria-hidden="true"></div>

		<header class="site-header">
			<a class="home-link" href="/">Sara Rajabzadeh</a>

			<nav aria-label="Primary navigation">
				<a href="/">Home</a>
				<a href="/projects" aria-current="page">Projects</a>
				<a href="/#contact">Contact</a>

				<a
					class="nav-resume"
					href={resumePath}
					target="_blank"
					rel="noreferrer"
				>
					Résumé
				</a>
			</nav>
		</header>

		<main>
			<section class="projects-hero">
				<p class="eyebrow">Selected projects</p>

				<h1>
					Research and engineering
					<span>across real-world vision problems.</span>
				</h1>

			</section>

			<section class="project-section" aria-labelledby="icm-title">
				<div class="project-copy">
					<div class="project-heading">
						<p class="project-number">01</p>

						<div>
							<p class="project-context">
								Paris Brain Institute · 2026
							</p>

							<h2 id="icm-title">
								Axon and myelin segmentation in electron microscopy
							</h2>
						</div>
					</div>

					<p>
						At the Paris Brain Institute, I am developing a complete
						deep-learning workflow for segmenting axons and myelin in
						transmission electron microscopy images. The objective is not only
						to produce accurate masks, but to build a reliable system that can
						improve through repeated annotation and retraining cycles.
					</p>

					<p>
						The pipeline combines manual annotation in Napari, nnU-Net v2
						fine-tuning, entropy-based active learning, and morphological and
						watershed-based post-processing. I also run preprocessing, training,
						and large-scale inference on a SLURM HPC cluster and evaluate the
						results using Dice, HD95, Panoptic Quality, and instance-level error
						analysis.
					</p>

					<ul class="tag-list" aria-label="ICM project technologies">
						{icmTags.map((tag) => <li>{tag}</li>)}
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="comparison">
					<figure>
						<div class="media-frame">
							<img
								src="/projects/icm/before-segmentation.webp"
								alt="Transmission electron microscopy before segmentation"
								loading="eager"
							/>
						</div>

						<figcaption>
							<span>Before</span>
							Raw electron microscopy image
						</figcaption>
					</figure>

					<figure>
						<div class="media-frame">
							<img
								src="/projects/icm/after-segmentation.webp"
								alt="Predicted axon and myelin segmentation over electron microscopy"
								loading="eager"
							/>
						</div>

						<figcaption>
							<span>After</span>
							Model prediction and post-processing
						</figcaption>
					</figure>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section
				class="project-section project-section-reversed"
				aria-labelledby="epfl-title"
			>
				<div class="project-copy">
					<div class="project-heading">
						<p class="project-number">02</p>

						<div>
							<p class="project-context">EPFL · 2021–2022</p>

							<h2 id="epfl-title">
								Diffusion models for robust 3D human pose forecasting
							</h2>
						</div>
					</div>

					<p>
						At EPFL, I worked on a diffusion-based approach for predicting
						future 3D human motion from incomplete and noisy observations.
						Instead of treating missing pose information as a separate
						preprocessing problem, the framework jointly repairs the observed
						sequence and generates plausible future motion.
					</p>

					<p>
						I contributed to developing and evaluating the temporally cascaded
						diffusion system under missing joints, missing frames, partial
						occlusions, and noisy pose estimates. The method was evaluated
						across Human3.6M, HumanEva-I, AMASS, and 3DPW and was published at
						ICRA 2023 after being presented at the NeurIPS 2022 Workshop on
						Score-Based Methods.
					</p>

					<ul class="tag-list" aria-label="EPFL project technologies">
						{epflTags.map((tag) => <li>{tag}</li>)}
					</ul>
				</div>

				<figure class="single-media">
					<div class="media-frame media-frame-wide">
						<img
							src="/projects/epfl/pose-forecasting.gif"
							alt="Animation demonstrating 3D human pose forecasting over time"
							loading="lazy"
						/>
					</div>

					<figcaption>
						<span>Pose forecasting</span>
						Observed motion and predicted future
						trajectories
					</figcaption>
				</figure>
			</section>

			<section class="project-section text-project" aria-labelledby="iqa-title">
				<div class="project-copy">
					<div class="project-heading">
						<p class="project-number">03</p>

						<div>
							<p class="project-context">
								Computer Vision Engineering · 2024–2025
							</p>

							<h2 id="iqa-title">
								Image and face quality assessment systems
							</h2>
						</div>
					</div>

					<p>
						I developed and benchmarked image-quality and face-quality
						assessment pipelines with a focus on understanding how models behave
						under realistic degradations—not only how they rank on a single
						benchmark. I evaluated sensitivity to blur, noise, illumination,
						exposure, occlusion, head pose, and motion.
					</p>

					<p>
						The work included comparing models such as TReS, OFIQ, GraFIQs,
						SDD-FIQA, and CR-FIQA, integrating RetinaFace and YOLOv8 detection,
						and studying how face cropping affected quality predictions. I also
						fine-tuned TReS across multiple datasets, investigated domain shift
						and overfitting, and deployed a GPU-backed inference service using
						FastAPI, Docker, CUDA, and Nginx.
					</p>

					<ul class="tag-list" aria-label="Image quality project technologies">
						{iqaTags.map((tag) => <li>{tag}</li>)}
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="project-details">
					<div>
						<span>Focus</span>
						<strong>Model behavior</strong>
						<p>
							Understanding failure modes across image distortions and
							real-world capture conditions.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<span>Engineering</span>
						<strong>Production inference</strong>
						<p>
							Reusable GPU model serving with API validation, tests, and
							optimized initialization.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<span>Evaluation</span>
						<strong>Generalization</strong>
						<p>
							Cross-dataset benchmarking using SRCC and PLCC to identify domain
							shift.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="project-section text-project" aria-labelledby="ucl-title">
				<div class="project-copy">
					<div class="project-heading">
						<p class="project-number">04</p>

						<div>
							<p class="project-context">
								University College London · 2022
							</p>

							<h2 id="ucl-title">
								Detecting neonatal bowel disease from abdominal X-rays
							</h2>
						</div>
					</div>

					<p>
						At University College London, I developed an EfficientNet-based
						system for detecting necrotizing enterocolitis from neonatal
						abdominal X-rays. The project required working carefully under
						limited-data conditions, where evaluation methodology and
						regularization were as important as the model architecture.
					</p>

					<p>
						I trained and evaluated the model on 62 patients using patient-level
						two-fold cross-validation, domain-specific augmentation, and
						regularization to reduce overfitting. The system achieved a mean F1
						score above 0.80, and I used Grad-CAM to examine whether predictions
						were associated with clinically relevant image regions.
					</p>

					<ul class="tag-list" aria-label="UCL project technologies">
						{uclTags.map((tag) => <li>{tag}</li>)}
					</ul>
				</div>

				<div class="project-details">
					<div>
						<span>Challenge</span>
						<strong>Limited clinical data</strong>
						<p>
							Patient-level validation was used to avoid leakage and produce a
							more realistic estimate of performance.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<span>Interpretability</span>
						<strong>Grad-CAM analysis</strong>
						<p>
							Model attention was reviewed to assess whether predictions were
							grounded in relevant anatomical regions.
						</p>
					</div>

					<div>
						<span>Result</span>
						<strong>Mean F1 above 0.80</strong>
						<p>
							Consistent performance across cross-validation folds despite the
							small clinical dataset.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section class="contact-section">
				<p class="eyebrow">Contact</p>

				<h2>Interested in working together?</h2>

				<p>
					I am open to computer vision, machine-learning engineering, medical AI,
					and applied research opportunities.
				</p>

				<a href="mailto:sara.rajabzadeh.1999@gmail.com">
					sara.rajabzadeh.1999@gmail.com
					<span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
				</a>
			</section>
		</main>

		<footer>
			<p>© {new Date().getFullYear()} Sara Rajabzadeh</p>
			<a href="/">Return to homepage</a>
		</footer>
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	:global(:root) {
		color-scheme: dark;
		--background: #07090d;
		--surface: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
		--surface-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.055);
		--border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
		--text: #f5f7fa;
		--muted: #9ba3b0;
		--accent: #7dd3fc;
		--accent-secondary: #a5b4fc;
	}

	:global(*) {
		box-sizing: border-box;
	}

	:global(html) {
		scroll-behavior: smooth;
	}

	:global(body) {
		margin: 0;
		min-width: 320px;
		background: var(--background);
		color: var(--text);
		font-family:
			Inter, ui-sans-serif, system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont,
			"Segoe UI", sans-serif;
		-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
	}

	:global(a) {
		color: inherit;
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.page-background {
		position: fixed;
		inset: 0;
		z-index: -1;
		pointer-events: none;
		background:
			radial-gradient(
				circle at 10% 0%,
				rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.11),
				transparent 30rem
			),
			radial-gradient(
				circle at 90% 20%,
				rgba(129, 140, 248, 0.09),
				transparent 34rem
			),
			linear-gradient(rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.022) 1px, transparent 1px),
			linear-gradient(
				90deg,
				rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.022) 1px,
				transparent 1px
			);
		background-size:
			auto,
			auto,
			64px 64px,
			64px 64px;
		mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, black 0%, transparent 85%);
	}

	.site-header,
	main,
	footer {
		width: min(1180px, calc(100% - 40px));
		margin-inline: auto;
	}

	.site-header {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		padding-block: 28px;
	}

	.home-link {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: -0.025em;
	}

	nav {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 27px;
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
	}

	nav a {
		transition: color 180ms ease;
	}

	nav a:hover,
	nav a[aria-current="page"] {
		color: var(--text);
	}

	.nav-resume {
		padding: 10px 15px;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 10px;
		color: var(--text);
	}

	.projects-hero {
		padding-block: clamp(95px, 13vw, 165px) 110px;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
	}

	.eyebrow,
	.project-context {
		margin: 0 0 16px;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.14em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}

	h1,
	h2,
	p {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	h1 {
		max-width: 970px;
		margin-bottom: 30px;
		font-size: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 6.2rem);
		line-height: 1;
		letter-spacing: -0.06em;
	}

	h1 span {
		display: block;
		background: linear-gradient(
			120deg,
			var(--text),
			var(--accent),
			var(--accent-secondary)
		);
		background-clip: text;
		color: transparent;
	}

	.hero-description {
		max-width: 790px;
		margin-bottom: 0;
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 2vw, 1.22rem);
		line-height: 1.75;
	}

	.project-section {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.9fr) minmax(0, 1.1fr);
		gap: clamp(45px, 7vw, 95px);
		align-items: center;
		padding-block: 125px;
		border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
	}

	.project-section-reversed .project-copy {
		order: 2;
	}

	.project-section-reversed .single-media {
		order: 1;
	}

	.project-heading {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 42px 1fr;
		gap: 12px;
		margin-bottom: 30px;
	}

	.project-number {
		margin: 4px 0 0;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, monospace;
		font-size: 0.78rem;
	}

	.project-context {
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	h2 {
		margin-bottom: 0;
		font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
		line-height: 1.08;
		letter-spacing: -0.045em;
	}

	.project-copy > p {
		color: var(--muted);
		line-height: 1.75;
	}

	.tag-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px;
		margin: 30px 0 0;
		padding: 0;
		list-style: none;
	}

	.tag-list li {
		padding: 7px 10px;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 999px;
		color: #b9c1cc;
		font-size: 0.75rem;
	}

	.comparison {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
		gap: 14px;
	}

	figure {
		margin: 0;
	}

	.media-frame {
		overflow: hidden;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 17px;
		background: var(--surface);
	}

	.media-frame img {
		display: block;
		width: 100%;
		aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
		object-fit: cover;
	}

	.media-frame-wide img {
		aspect-ratio: 16 / 10;
		object-fit: contain;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
	}

	figcaption {
		margin-top: 13px;
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: 0.78rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	figcaption span {
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 4px;
		color: var(--text);
		font-weight: 600;
	}

	.text-project {
		align-items: start;
	}

	.project-details {
		display: grid;
		gap: 13px;
	}

	.project-details div {
		padding: 25px;
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: 16px;
		background: var(--surface);
	}

	.project-details span {
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 10px;
		color: var(--accent);
		font-size: 0.7rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 0.12em;
		text-transform: uppercase;
	}

	.project-details strong {
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 9px;
		font-size: 1.05rem;
	}

	.project-details p {
		margin-bottom: 0;
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: 0.9rem;
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	.contact-section {
		padding-block: 135px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.contact-section h2 {
		max-width: 760px;
		margin-inline: auto;
		margin-bottom: 23px;
	}

	.contact-section > p:not(.eyebrow) {
		max-width: 620px;
		margin: 0 auto 34px;
		color: var(--muted);
		line-height: 1.75;
	}

	.contact-section > a {
		display: inline-flex;
		gap: 9px;
		padding-bottom: 5px;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(125, 211, 252, 0.45);
		color: var(--accent);
		font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.2rem);
	}

	footer {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		padding-block: 35px;
		border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
		color: var(--muted);
		font-size: 0.8rem;
	}

	footer p {
		margin: 0;
	}

	:global(a:focus-visible) {
		outline: 2px solid var(--accent);
		outline-offset: 5px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 850px) {
		.project-section {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.project-section-reversed .project-copy,
		.project-section-reversed .single-media {
			order: initial;
		}

		.project-section .project-copy {
            max-width: 760px;
        }

        .project-section .single-media {
            width: 100%;
        }
	}

	@media (max-width: 620px) {
		.site-header,
		main,
		footer {
			width: min(100% - 28px, 1180px);
		}

		.site-header {
			align-items: flex-start;
			gap: 20px;
		}

		.home-link {
			display: none;
		}

		nav {
			width: 100%;
			justify-content: flex-end;
			gap: 12px;
			font-size: 0.8rem;
		}

		.nav-resume {
			padding: 8px 10px;
		}

		.projects-hero {
			padding-top: 85px;
		}

		h1 {
			font-size: clamp(2.75rem, 14vw, 4rem);
		}

		.project-section {
			padding-block: 90px;
		}

		.comparison {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.project-heading {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}

		.project-number {
			margin-bottom: 2px;
		}

		footer {
			flex-direction: column;
			gap: 10px;
		}
	}

	@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
		:global(html) {
			scroll-behavior: auto;
		}

		nav a {
			transition: none;
		}
	}
</style>